<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Articles</td><form method='post' action=''><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Articles</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/starwarsccg/articles/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/lotr/articles/articles.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/articles/articles.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/articles/articles.php'>Star Wars TCG</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Signet Reference Document<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.22)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=11688'>John "Skeeter" Drinkwater</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=11688&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> August 20, 2002</font><p align='justify'><font class="bfont"> This is not a definitive or opinionated article as such, but I thought just to document the <br>
<br>
signet characteristics of the fellowship cards in a reference article.  I am a collector and casual player and this psuedo-article was inspired by my collection of fellowship cards that I placed together in my album based on signets, not card number, culture or expansion set.<br>
<br>
Frodo Signet :-<br>
<br>
1) 1C290 Frodo, Son of Drogo - Exert another Companion with Frodo signet to heal Frodo.<br>
2) 1R310 Sam, Faithful Companion - Play Bill the Pony from draw deck.<br>
3) 1C306 Pippin, Friend to Frodo - Opponent may not discard hobbit culture tales from play.<br>
4) 1R302 Merry, Friend to Sam - If Merry not assigned to skirmish, exert twice to add his strength to another companion (skirmish phase).<br>
5) 1R72 Gandalf, Friend of the ShireFolk - Gandalf + 1 strength for each race.<br>
6) 3R38 Aragorn, Heir to the White City - remove (2) each time Fellowship moves in Fellowship phase.<br>
7) 1U97 Boromir, Son of Denethor - exert Boromir to make a Hobbit strength + 3.<br>
8) 1R50 Legolas Greenleaf - exert for direct wound (archery phase).<br>
9) 2P121 Gimli, Dwarf of the Mountain Race - Underground site shadow number is -2.<br>
x) 3U7 Arwen, Elven Rider - discard 3 cards to prevent wound to Ring-bearer.<br>
<br>
Aragorn signet :-<br>
<br>
1) 2C102 Frodo, Reluctant Adventurer - cost of some items played on Frodo is -1.<br>
2) 1C311 Sam, Son of Hamfast - exert to remove burden (Fellowship phase).<br>
3) 2C110 Pippin, Mr. Took - Play Gandalf or Aragorn for twilight cost -2.<br>
4) 1C303 Merry, from o&#39;er the Brandywine - Merry strength +2 whilst bearing a weapon.<br>
5) 2P122 Gandalf, Grey Pilgrim - draw a card at the start of each turn.<br>
6) 1P365 Aragorn, King in Exile - at start of turn heal another companion with Aragorn signet.<br>
7) 1R96 Boromir, Lord of Gondor - Boromir not overwhelmed unless strength tripled.<br>
8) 3P121 Legolas, Son of Thranduil - add 1 to archery total at river or forest.<br>
9) 1U12 Gimli, Dwarf of Erebor - add (2) to place a card from hand beneath draw deck (beware text change of this card - now allowed only if twilight pool is less than 2).<br>
x) 1R30 Arwen, Daughter of Elrond - strength + 3 skirmishing against a Nazgul.<br>
<br>
Gandalf Signet :-<br>
<br>
1) 1R289 Frodo, Old Bilbo&#39;s Heir - heal Hobbit ally start of each turn.<br>
2) 2C114 Sam, Proper Poet - exert to make Sam defender + 1.<br>
3) 1R307 Pippin, Hobbit of some Intelligence - when played may remove a wound or burden.<br>
4) 2C104 Merry, Horticulturalist - exert Merry to play Farmer Maggot from draw deck.<br>
5) 1P364 Gandalf, Grey Wizard - exert to play companion with Gandalf signet for twilight -2.<br>
6) 1R89 Aragorn, Ranger of the North - exert to make Aragorn defender + 1.<br>
7) 3P122 Boromir, Defender of Minas Tirith - add (2) to heal Boromir.<br>
8) 1U51 Legolas, Prince of Mirkwood - strength + 3 whilst skirmishing Nazgul.<br>
9) 1R13 Gimli, Son of Gloin - exert to make strength + 2.<br>
x) 3R8 Arwen, Lady Undomiel - spot 3 home site 3 elf allies, Arwen is strength + 3.<br>
<br>
Comments :-  clearly there is no theme consistency in the signets - this, I assume, is a deliberate design feature.  It would have been interesting to see additional thematic <br>
<br>
features in the signet partnerships though, eg. twilight denial in one signet, power-up specials in another, perhaps burden resistance or deck cycling in the third but the way the signet partnerships are currently creates the deck design dilemma of &quot;do I go for the signet partnership or do I break the partnership for thematic design?&quot;<br>
<br>
Appendix :-  in this final section I have listed the few cards (as I found them) that specifically work with the signet partnership.<br>
<br>
1C290 Frodo, Son of Drogo - the Frodo signet is used to allow this Frodo (wearing the Frodo signet) to be healed by exerting another companion with a Frodo signet.<br>
<br>
1P364 Gandalf, The Grey Wizard - exert this Gandalf (wearing the Gandalf signet) to play another companion with a Gandalf signet for a twilight cost -2.<br>
<br>
1P265 Aragorn, King in Exile - at start of your turn heal one other companion that is wearing the Aragorn signet.<br>
<br>
2C23 Gandalf&#39;s Wisdom (condition) - twilight cost of each possession or artifact played on Gandalf or companion wearing Gandalf signet is -1.<br>
<br>
2R36 No Mere Ranger - exert Aragorn to make another companion strength +2 (or strength +3 if they wear a Aragorn signet)<br>
<br>
3U35 Trust me as you Once did (condition) - exert Gandalf to make a companion strength +1 for each companion with the Gandalf signet (limit +3)<br>
<br>
3U47 Voice of Rauros (event) - exert Aragorn to make each companion wearing the Aragorn signet damage + 1 (maneuver phase)<br>
<br>
